cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on routing in delay tolerant networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the presence of heterogeneity in inter-contact time distributions, which is related to the social behavior of nodes in the network. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces a stochastic model and analytically derives the mean delivery time, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus, the paper briefly mentions the security implications of routing in DTNs. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper discusses how exploiting user diversity can improve routing performance.
